(248, 1, '2011-05-17 18:55:15', '2011-05-17 18:55:15', '<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-I9wKa-Lp3sQ/TdNNHj5x-TI/AAAAAAAAACE/HgZyz1FQIWA/s400/afghanistan_comic.jpg"><img class="alignnone" title="Plan Ink" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-I9wKa-Lp3sQ/TdNNHj5x-TI/AAAAAAAAACE/HgZyz1FQIWA/s400/afghanistan_comic.jpg" alt="" width="363" height="400" /></a>\r\n\r\nThere are almost 1 billion illiterate people in the world. Or, if you prefer, 1 out of 7. Hard to believe, right?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnd it is even harder if you consider the fact that literacy is a basic prerequisite in order to function in our current society: from asserting your voting rights to getting a job, from honing your professional skills to being able to understand how to take medicine. No matter how you look at it, literacy is a basic human right and a prerequisite for reaching one’s full potential.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith this clear in mind – and after a six-month stint spent working on children’s textbooks with the UN in Afghanistan – I decided to launch Plain Ink, a publishing social enterprise that harnesses the power of books and storytelling to spark change globally.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPlain Ink employs a visual methodology to teach children and adults about areas such as health, food security, gender equality, disaster mitigation and others in an engaging, straightforward and appealing way: comics. Yes, comics: learning while enjoying it is an effective way to make sure that what you’re learning stays with you forever.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStarting with comics being produced for India and Afghanistan, Plain Ink has created an unique layout that offers, on the same page, graphic-only messages and basic texts in the local languages,to reach out to those with limited skills as well as those with no literacy skills at all. Our first comics, dealing with Health, Nutrition, Wat/San and Hygiene present clear messages through the adventures of a group of committed children, in an entertaining way.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe comics are piloted with different stakeholders locally and with area experts, and are printed locally in order to contribute to the creative economy of the locale they will be distributed to.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSee more examples of the bright, engaging and captivating books at PlainInk.org\r\n\r\n<a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-rK3B1KkauhM/TdNNtt-TlFI/AAAAAAAAACM/JP8CJwkTsGU/s400/Picture%2B1.png"><img class="alignnone" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-rK3B1KkauhM/TdNNtt-TlFI/AAAAAAAAACM/JP8CJwkTsGU/s400/Picture%2B1.png" alt="" width="400" height="367" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-3QEG2fuL_hw/TdNONjtAGOI/AAAAAAAAACU/nDTY1djQ8lE/s400/Picture%2B2.png"><img class="alignnone" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-3QEG2fuL_hw/TdNONjtAGOI/AAAAAAAAACU/nDTY1djQ8lE/s400/Picture%2B2.png" alt="" width="400" height="177" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Plain Ink – when change reads like a (comic) book', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'plain-ink-when-change-reads-like-a-comic-book', '', '', '2012-10-31 18:55:54', '2012-10-31 18:55:54', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=248', 0, 'post', '', 0),
