(270, 1, '2011-01-17 19:52:37', '2011-01-17 19:52:37', '<div>Last week BRUTE LABS had the pleasure of hosting MICA''s (Maryland Institute College of Design) Mike Weikert and Ryan Clifford.  During their visit they shared the story behind, and their plans for, MICA''s exciting new <a href="http://www.mica.edu/Programs_of_Study/MA_Degree_Programs/Social_Design_%28MA%29.html">Social Design Master''s Program</a>.  Our own Josh To, is serving as a faculty advisor to the program, along with John Bielenberg and Emily Pilloton, among others.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Mike, the director of the new program, puts it best: "There is a growing interest and understanding in the world of design related to the designer''s role and responsibility in society, specifically the belief that social change can happen through design.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The Master of Arts in Social Design (MASD) prepares students to play a vital role in positively impacting our world through collaborative, hands-on opportunities supporting a range of community-defined objectives."</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The new program makes it''s home, <a href="http://www.mica.edu/Programs_of_Study/MA_Degree_Programs/Social_Design_%28MA%29/MICA_PLACE.html">MICA PLACE</a>, in East Baltimore in a newly renovated 24,000 sq foot building that was once the chancellery and school of the St. Wenceslaus Church.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xydTRd18G4Y/TTSnrdrAnXI/AAAAAAAAAD4/QdZopkVpPL0/s1600/MICA_Place.png"><img class="alignnone" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xydTRd18G4Y/TTSnrdrAnXI/AAAAAAAAAD4/QdZopkVpPL0/s1600/MICA_Place.png" alt="" width="468" height="351" /></a></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>BRUTE LABS is looking forward to the innovative stuff coming out of East Baltimore (and can''t wait to visit MICA PLACE on our next trip East).</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Want to learn more about MICA''s new program