(49, 2, 'bio', 'Born in SF and a lifelong Bay Area resident, I love big ideas and am passionate about the role that design and technology plays in business and humanitarian projects. Always on the move, I founded BRUTE LABS because it gives me a great excuse to jump from one thing to another, meet new people, and find myself in interesting situations. I strive to motivate my peers and strongly believe in collaboration for the greater good. My other passions include bargain shopping (bought a brand-new pair of jeans for 54 cents), distance running (recently completed a 50K) and travel (am dying to go to Patagonia.)'),
