(63, 3, 'bio', 'After graduating college in 2005 I started working in advertising. My job was challenging and new but something was also missing. Co-founding BRUTE LABS became my post-academic outlet for creative energy. What I lacked in project management or non-profit experience, I made up for with enthusiasm. BRUTE LABS immediately became an environment where I was surrounded with smarter, better organized and more qualified peers. Now I''m challenged to work harder, step outside my comfort zone and be a better global citizen every week. I''m proud of the lives we''ve touched from East Palo Alto to rural Ghana and can''t wait to launch our next 12 projects.'),
