(85, 4, 'bio', 'For me, BRUTE LABS is a first. As it turns out, it''s one of my guiltiest pleasures. Nothing nourishes the soul like seeing a problem and being part of the solution. I look at my life, and I have plenty. Plenty of food, water and shelter. More than enough to share. It''s easy to forget that I''m not busting my ass every day just to stay alive. More often than not, that''s the lot that people have in this world. Relative to them, I have an eternity of leisure - the luxury of time. Hell yeah I have time to help out. Damn straight you do too. My venture into the world of altruism was by invitation. I probably would never have found my way, were it not for that invitation. May my words serve as an invitation to you.'),
