(151, 6, 'bio', 'For me, BRUTE LABS is a way to bring real change to the world I inhabit. I''ve worked in the music industry, in high tech and advertising, but I''ve never felt as fulfilled as I do when I''m working on a project with the BRUTE LABS team. Being a twentysomething American I am incredibly lucky compared with someone born into a developing nation. With BRUTE LABS, I can work to level the playing field. It''s with great pride that I have worked with the BRUTE LABS team to provide relief to Myanmar, drill wells in Ghana and provided much needed information about local resources to the homeless population in Santa Monica.'),
