(195, 9, 'bio', 'It''s a challenge to step back and view the world in a larger context. It''s an even greater challenge to actually act on that new perspective day in and day out. For me, BRUTE LABS is an incredible opportunity to work with some of the most talented and ambitious people I''ve ever met, to focus our efforts on improving people''s lives and in the process bettering ourselves. My path to BRUTE LABS took me from my home in Virginia to school in Rhode Island, a job with a composer in New York City, and then out to San Francisco where I currently work in Silicon Valley. When I''m not working on BRUTE LABS projects, I like to make simple recordings on my tape recorder, play tennis and softball, and cook the two things I cook well (banana bread and baked ziti).'),
