(217, 10, 'bio', 'When I learned of BRUTE LABS and its philosophy of just getting things done, big or small, close to home or halfway around the globe, there was no debate over whether or not to get involved. The answer was obvious. The world we inhabit is full of challenges, problems, and impending disasters. Increasingly the news media, the government, and the entertainment industry, go to great lengths to make us all acutely aware of how awful everything is. Very rarely does anyone actually seem to provide concrete solutions for how to improve the situation of those most at risk, or that of humanity at large. It can be more than a bit overwhelming. Flashy movies and daunting statistics serve to either depress us, or temporarily ignite our desire to take action...only...we often don''t know what action to take and find our motivation displaced by a sense of helplessness. With BRUTE, I''m finally able to take a direct hand in the changing the world for the better, a little at time.'),
