(239, 11, 'bio', 'As a long time Bay Area resident, I had been searching for ways to become more involved in my community and abroad. My search took me no further than the next cubicle when I met the core team members of Brute Labs. Collaborating with Brute Labs has become the most exciting and stimulating part of my day. Surrounded by passionate people with infectious energy gives us the enthusiasm we need to create solutions for many local and global issues. Though the group is small, no idea or solution is too big for us to solve. The Brutes have taught me to always think big, present interesting design elements to our cause, but most importantly, arm our communities with the basics they need to succeed. During some Brutish downtime, you can find me in any independent movie theater watching as many films as I can, attending film festivals, going to the theater, traveling, wandering through museums, searching for the best cup of espresso, and falling off of my skateboard.'),
