(359, 15, 'bio', 'Born and raised in the Bay Area – a place known for endless opportunities – I’ve seen too many people struggle to reach their full potential. The great ethnic and socioeconomic diversity of this area has instilled in me the belief that everyone, no matter where they come from, deserves the opportunity to succeed. I joined BRUTE LABS to really explore how understanding and action can break down barriers (and to meet talented like-minded peers in the process). This challenge has also found its way into my career in public relations where understanding different points of view and finding common ground are fundamental. When I’m not working, I enjoy yogalates (to keep me sane), great food and friends, and shopping (it’s an art).'),
