(377, 17, 'bio', 'Scott’s Palo Alto roots, Stanford education, and work at Google and Facebook paint him as a “townie” for all but those who know him. A big ideas guy, entrepreneur, and adventurer, he’s also lived and worked on five continents. His background between street shelters in Ecuador, the State Department in Geneva, White House in Washington, and Google in India and Africa have framed his perspective that private sector business development is the surest means to sustainable development. His joint degree policy and business studies at Columbia, while distracting him from the Financial Times and Ironman 70.3 triathlon training, also give him time to watch Spanish football and ride his beach cruiser barefoot, two of his foremost passions.'),
