(386, 18, 'bio', 'As a recent San Francisco transplant, I was looking for a group of young, motivated and passionate individuals who were looking to make progress in the world and take risks. I had known about BRUTE LABS prior to my move the Bay Area and became instantly impressed with the talent among the BRUTE LABS team and its collaborative partners upon my first meeting. Since my first BRUTE introduction I’ve been fortunate enough to collaborate on project IGoR and San Francisco’s iteration of projectOPEN. In my free time, you can probably find me drinking coffee and eating chocolate croissant in the Mission, or spending much of my disposable income at one of the many SF thrift stores.'),
