(293, 1, '2010-11-17 20:35:04', '2010-11-17 20:35:04', '<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_RKhHytFfgS0/TOR7YBZil2I/AAAAAAAABb4/PH6LuHm_9R4/s1600/FlipMovember.jpg"><img class="alignnone" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_RKhHytFfgS0/TOR7YBZil2I/AAAAAAAABb4/PH6LuHm_9R4/s320/FlipMovember.jpg" alt="" width="295" height="200" /></a>\r\n\r\nI first learned about <strong>BRUTE LABS</strong> at a talk at Red Rock Coffee in Mountain View called Small Talks, Big Ideas: <strong>BRUTE LABS</strong>. I have worked with them on a project lending my illustration services and am excited to work with them in the future. It’s easy to support a design team that designs for the good of the world. They invited me to share a bit about a project that I’m working on that is also for a good cause: Movember.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI just started a new job at Cisco Consumer Products – Flip Video as their graphic designer/ online merchandiser. We make Flip Video Cameras, and they have customizable faceplates, which is really useful when trying to send an important message. We have a section on our site called Flip for Good where a portion of proceeds supports a nonprofit or charity. This month we are featuring Movember.\r\n<strong>What is Movember?</strong>\r\nMovember is an annual charity event held during the month of November, where men grow a moustache to raise awareness and funds for cancers affecting men.\r\n<strong>Team Cisco</strong> is recruiting employees around the globe to join the effort and commit to growing a moustache for the month of November and raise money to fight cancer. The women of Cisco also participate by joining a team, donating to a team, wearing fake moustaches (optional), and talking about the event.\r\n<div></div>\r\n<strong>How Do I Donate Directly?</strong>\r\nClick here:\r\n<a href="http://us.movember.com/donate/your-details/member_id/599330/">http://us.movember.com/donate/your-details/member_id/599330/</a>\r\nand then fill out your information.\r\nWe will be posting regular updates of our Mo growing progress and funds raised on the Flip Video Facebook and Twitter pages and throughout the Cisco network.\r\n<strong>How do I buy a Stash-tastic Flip Camera and donate at the same time?</strong>\r\nBuy a custom Movember Flip video camera at <a href="http://www.theflip.com/movember">www.theflip.com/movember</a> which generates a $10 donation to the Movember foundation to fight cancer.\r\n<div><strong>Why get involved?</strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>-A man is 35% more likely to be diagnosed with prostate cancer than a woman is to be diagnosed with breast cancer.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>- A man will die from prostate cancer every 16.4 minutes- 32,000 men will die of the disease this year.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>- 1 in 6 men will be diagnosed with prostate cancer- more than 218,000 cases of prostate cancer are expected to be diagnosed this year.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>- The men’s health movement is 30 years behind the women’s health movement.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>', 'Movember!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'movember', '', '', '2012-10-31 20:44:44', '2012-10-31 20:44:44', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=293', 0, 'post', '', 0),
